        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 6:44PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Slapout, or 15 miles southwest of Laverne, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Follett and Slapout.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
